 Asian Games}}\n\nSaudi Arabia entered fourteen athletes (11 men's and 3 women's) to participate in the athletics competition at the Games.<ref>{{cite web |title=Official Result Book Athletics |url=http://www.ocagames.com/orb/files/4/62/AG2018_OfficialResultBook_Athletics_v1.1.pdf |publisher=[[Olympic Council of Asia]] |date=30 August 2018 |accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Badminton ==\n{{main article|Badminton at the 2018 Asian Games}}\n\n;Women\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:90%;text-align:center\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!Round of 32\n!Round of 16\n!Quarterfinals\n!Semifinals\n!colspan=\"2\"|Final\n|-\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Rank\n|-\n|align=left| Rana Abu Harbesh\n|align=center rowspan=2| [[Badminton at the 2018 Asian Games \u2013 Women's singles|Singles]]\n|{{flagIOC2athlete|[[Cheung Ngan Yi|Cheung N Y]]|HKG|2018 Asian Games}}<br />'''L''' 2\u201321, 5\u201321\n|colspan=5|Did not advance\n|-\n|align=left| Shatha Almutairi\n|{{flagIOC2athlete|[[Kavidi Sirimannage|K Sirimannage]]|SRI|2018 Asian Games}}<br />'''L''' 4\u201321, 4\u201321\n|colspan=5|Did not advance\n|-\n|align=left| Rana Abu Harbesh <br /> Shatha Almutairi\n|align=center| [[Badminton at the 2018 Asian Games \u2013 Women's doubles|Doubles]]\n|{{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOC2athlete|[[Lee So-hee|Lee S-h]] / <br />[[Shin Seung-chan|Shin S-c]]|KOR|2018 Asian Games}}<br />'''L''' 4\u201321, 7\u201321\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|}\n\n== Bowling ==\n{{Main article|Bowling at the 2018 Asian Games}}\n\n;Men\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:90%;text-align:center\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!Block 1\n!Block 2\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Total\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Rank\n|- style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Result\n!Result\n|-\n|align=left|Adel Al-Bariqi<br />Sultan Al-Masri<br />Ammar Tarrad\n|align=left rowspan=2|[[Bowling at the 2018 Asian Games \u2013 Men's trios|Trios]]\n|2000\n